cated where we are in the lower Mississippi River, we also see over 
60  percent  of  the  grain  exports  from  mid-America  and  America’s 
bread  basket  come  right  through  the  lower  Mississippi  River  and 
right  through  New  Orleans  and  the  other  ports  on  the  river  as 
well, from the Port of South Louisiana. 

New  Orleans  also,  according  to  the  International  Council  of 
