58 

on the many scientists and clinicians working in New Orleans that 
impact the entire country. 

In  closing,  I  thank  you  for  visiting  us  here  in  New  Orleans.  It’s 
important  that  you’re  actually  here,  on  the  ground.  And  I  know 
that  Senator  Vitter  and  Senator  Landrieu  have  worked  very  hard 
along with the rest of the delegation to get you all here, and I know 
that you’ve seen the devastation, and we’re living it everyday. And 
we’re  simply  asking  you  not  for  a  handout,  but  simply  a  hand  up 
as  we  rebuild  the  city.  We’re  committed  to  rebuilding.  We’re  not 
asking you to do everything, but we do know that without the Fed-
eral Government’s help it will be much more difficult. So we’re sim-
ply  asking  you  for  assistance  at  this  time.  Thank  you  very  much. 

